The paper deals with speech enhancement using generative adversarial networks, which involves signal processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SD (Sound), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves natural language processing. The paper also involves training a GAN, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning), and the use of objective and subjective evaluations, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
